    <h2>Introduction</h2>

    <!-- Main Goals -->
    <h3>Main Goals for the Portfolio:</h3>
    <p><strong>Objective:</strong> The primary goal of this portfolio is to showcase my comprehensive understanding of web application security concepts and demonstrate practical implementations of security measures in web development.</p>
    
    <!-- Key Focus Areas -->
    <h3>Key Focus Areas:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Security Knowledge:</strong> Present a solid grasp of key concepts such as secure coding practices, encryption, authentication, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Practical Implementation:</strong> Showcase real-world examples of implementing web application security measures.</li>
        <li><strong>Critical Thinking:</strong> Highlight my ability to think critically about security challenges and propose effective solutions.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Major Lessons Learned -->
    <h3>Major Lessons Learned:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Self-Discovery:</strong> Throughout the creation of this portfolio, I have discovered a deeper understanding of my passion for web application security and its significance in today's digital landscape.</li>
        <li><strong>Acquired Skills:</strong> The process has equipped me with practical skills in implementing security measures, from coding practices to the architectural aspects of secure web applications.</li>
        <li><strong>Critical and Creative Thinking:</strong> The journey has enhanced my critical thinking abilities, enabling me to analyze security issues and propose creative solutions to safeguard web applications from potential threats.</li>
    </ul>
</section>
